result.execSummary:
The defendant Akeem Shamar Cole was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Drive or Operate Vehicle w/o Consent, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.23(3).
  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Attorney Ann M Heaps in court, Defendant Akeem Shamar Cole not in court, in custody (in bull pen).  Denis John Stingl appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  On motion of the State the Court set the Restitution at ZERO. No objection from Defense.
Associated with Charge #1

Defendant Akeem Shamar Cole in court with attorney Ann M Heaps.  Defendant Akeem Shamar Cole in custody.  Antonella Aleman appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court finds State has complied with victim notification.  Sentencing hearing proceeds.  Statements made as to sentencing.  

AS TO COUNT 1: The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 2 YEARS AND 6 MONTHS (CONSECUTIVE TO COUNT 2 AND ANY OTHER SENTENCE), with credit for 151 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 1 YEAR AND 6 MONTHS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 1 YEAR.  
AS TO COUNT 2: The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 2 YEARS AND 6 MONTHS (CONSECUTIVE TO COUNT 1 AND ANY OTHER SENTENCE); the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 1 YEAR AND 6 MONTHS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 1 YEAR.  
The defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program after serving 3 years of combined prison sentences and is not eligible for the "Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program".

Defendant shall provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs.
Court ordered defendant to pay all applicable court costs and surcharges.
As to all costs and surcharges, Court orders DOC shall collect up to 25% of prison funds.  Remaining balance to be paid during the period of extended supervision.  Unpaid portion to convert to a civil judgment.  
Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm or body armor. Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended and he may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored. 

As to restitution, Court sets this matter for restitution hearing.  Defendant authorized counsel to appear on his behalf for purposes of restitution hearing.  Victim to provide verification of expenses incurred and that damages to vehicle were a result of this incident.  Restitution hearing scheduled for July 22, 2016 at 08:30 am.
